snippet.title: 7 Night Wilderness Camping Adventure With My Dog [EXTENDED VERSION] (Part 1 of 3)
snippet.description:
I head out into the wilderness with my dog, Monty, to spend a week canoeing, portaging, fishing, eating and viewing wildlife and the beautiful nature. We encounter all sorts of weather and have a blast!

This is the extended version of the trip, to see the other parts, or to watch the shortened version in one video visit the following links!
Extended Version Part 2: (Not Yet Released!)
Extended Version Part 3: (Not Yet Released!)
Condensed Version: https://youtu.be/VCy4bZt9JKc

Permethrin Tips
Always follow directions when using permethrin as it is very toxic in its liquid form. It is extremely toxic to cats! Wear rubber gloves and be careful until it fully adheres to your clothing.
The brand I use is Martins. I dilute it at a ratio of 19 parts water to 1 part Martins permethrin. I completely soak all gear in a 5 gallon bucket of this solution for perfect coverage. I do all clothing, then get some on my muckboot foam top part, my tent, and a bandanna for Monty. I have tested it with finding a tick and letting the tick crawl on my treated clothes and the tick died within 10 minutes.

snippet.title: 7 Night Wilderness Camping Adventure With My Dog [FULL TRIP]
snippet.description:
I head out into the wilderness with my dog, Monty, to spend a week canoeing, portaging, fishing, eating and viewing wildlife and the beautiful nature. We encounter all sorts of weather and have a blast!

Extended Version Part 1: (Not Yet Released!)
Extended Version Part 2: (Not Yet Released!)
Extended Version Part 3: (Not Yet Released!)

Permethrin Tips
Always follow directions when using permethrin as it is very toxic in its liquid form. It is extremely toxic to cats! Wear rubber gloves and be careful until it fully adheres to your clothing.
The brand I use is Martins. I dilute it at a ratio of 19 parts water to 1 part Martins permethrin. I completely soak all gear in a 5 gallon bucket of this solution for perfect coverage. I do all clothing, then get some on my muckboot foam top part, my tent, and a bandanna for Monty. I have tested it with finding a tick and letting the tick crawl on my treated clothes and the tick died within 10 minutes.

localized.title: 7 Night Wilderness Camping Adventure With My Dog [FULL TRIP]
localized.description:
I head out into the wilderness with my dog, Monty, to spend a week canoeing, portaging, fishing, eating and viewing wildlife and the beautiful nature. We encounter all sorts of weather and have a blast!

Extended Version Part 1: (Not Yet Released!)
Extended Version Part 2: (Not Yet Released!)
Extended Version Part 3: (Not Yet Released!)

Permethrin Tips
Always follow directions when using permethrin as it is very toxic in its liquid form. It is extremely toxic to cats! Wear rubber gloves and be careful until it fully adheres to your clothing.
The brand I use is Martins. I dilute it at a ratio of 19 parts water to 1 part Martins permethrin. I completely soak all gear in a 5 gallon bucket of this solution for perfect coverage. I do all clothing, then get some on my muckboot foam top part, my tent, and a bandanna for Monty. I have tested it with finding a tick and letting the tick crawl on my treated clothes and the tick died within 10 minutes.

I head out with my dog Monty for a weeklong adventure in the wilderness. We set up camp at a new site every night and try to catch fish for dinner. We portage from lake to lake and have a great time.

This video is the extended version of the trip and is part 1 of a 5 part series.
For The shortened condensed highlight version of the trip, click here!: (NOT YET AVAILABLE! THIS VERSION WILL BE RELEASED AFTER ALL 5 PARTS OF THE EXTENDED SERIES HAS BEEN RELEASED!)

*Steak Quesadilla Fajita*
Ingredients:
Equal portions of-
Green Pepper
White Onion
Mushroom
Thinly Cut Steak (Any kind)
Large Tortilla
Queso Cheese
Butter
Sour Cream
Salsa

Fajita Sauce:
Minced Garlic
1 1/2 Teaspoons Salt
1 Tablespoon Cumin
1/2 Teaspoon Chili Powder
1/2 Teaspoon Crushed Red Pepper
2 Tablespoons Olive Oil
Lemon Juice from 1 lemon
1/3 Cup A1 Steak Sauce
1/2 Tablespoon Corn Starch

Cooking:
Heat a large cast iron skillet on high heat, let get very hot.
Once Hot, throw in about 2 tablespoons of butter, and immediately after throw in steak, peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Cook for roughly 5 minutes or until everything is slightly cooked, stirring constantly.

Pile all food onto one side of the skillet and drizzle fajita sauce over top. 2 Spoonfuls for light flavor, 3 for medium, and 4 for heavy fajita flavor.

After 30 seconds, mix fajita sauce and pepper onion meat mixture around on pan stirring constantly.

Meanwhile place large tortilla ina  apan with a little olive oil, on medium heat. Sprinkle queso cheese all over tortilla.

After cooking the peppers onions and meat for a couple more minutes, take off heat when a char has developed on the outside of the food.

Put pepper onion meat mixture into tortilla on one half, fold over. Cut into quarters.
Serve with Sour Cream and Salsa.
ENJOY!

snippet.title: How to Make Your Own Dehydrated Camping Meals - Dehydrated Spaghetti
snippet.description:
I show you how to make your own dehydrated meals for camping! They save you money, have larger portions and taste better than buying the meals from the store! I show you how I make my dehydrated spaghetti in this episode! It's very simple to make!

Recipe Ingredients:
1 Large Green Bell Pepper
1 Large Red Bell Pepper
1 Medium White Onion
1 small package of Baby Bella Mushrooms
2 Pounds of Lean Ground Beef
5 Cans of 24 Ounce Hunts Traditional Pasta Sauce (I use 4 in the video but 5 are recommended)
3 Pounds of Spaghetti Noodles

Spices: These numbers and measurements are a guesstimate, I never actually measure these
3  Tablespoons Basil Leaf
2 Tablespoons Oregano
3 Tablespoons Black Pepper
3 Tablespoons Dark Brown Sugar
3 Tablespoons Dried Minced Garlic or Garlic Powder
1/2 Tablespoon Cayenne Pepper
1/2 Tablespoon Salt

1. Subscribe to the channel

snippet.title: 10 Days (Almost) Alone in the Wilderness - Part 3 of 3
snippet.description:
I head out with my dog Monty on a 10 day solo adventure in the wilderness during the fall. I portage over 60 times through lakes and rivers. I sweat, I bleed and I eat some fish. 

This portion of the trip covers nights 8 and 9. I have an amazing encounter with a bull moose, get trapped in some nasty weather and search for my old pal, Larry.

Listed below are time links to each morning:
Morning of Day 9:      36:50 
Morning of Day 10: 1:04:12 

Click here for part 1!: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2OQuCGCoMWE
Click here for part 2!: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gd6pEmjNo-w

Note about the audio: This is the one and only time I use the GoPro Hero 5. I upgraded right before this trip to the hero 5 and the audio on it was insanely over sensitive and that is why there is a lot of background noise. As soon as I got home and checked my footage I was very disappointed so I returned the gopro hero 5. Then the hero 6 came out and I purchased that so the audio should never be this bad again!

snippet.title: The Dog Treat Song
snippet.description:
A song about a dog and a treat.

Part of the reason I uploaded this video was to raise awareness of a condition called, "Dog Bloat." The dog in this video, Hachi, passed away due to this condition.

Dog bloat caused Hachi's stomach to flip, which is called, "Gastric Dilatation Volvulus." We did all we could to save him and even after surgery we lost him. Learn the signs as early detection is key in saving your dogs life. Ask your vet about preventing this condition. If we had known more, he'd still be he with us.

This was actually a practice run for this song but we never got a chance to do another take.

Thank you for watching!

Follow me on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/matthewposa/

Learn the signs as early detection is key in saving your dogs life. Ask your vet about preventing this condition. If we had known more, he'd still be he with us.

This was actually a practice run for this song but we never got a chance to do another take.

Thank you for watching!

snippet.title: Lake Superior Otters Try to Steal My Fish at Isle Royale
snippet.description:
During one of the last days of our first 2 week camping trip on Isle Royale, we had to paddle about 8 miles. During that time I caught a 10 lb king salmon and had paddled at least 6 miles with it on my stringer and it created a ton of drag.

When we got to camp, I tied off my fish to the dock and put it down in the water to keep it cold. When I came back later to check on it, it was gone. I knew the culprit, Otters.

I went out fishing the next day and caught 2 Lake Trout. This time I knew better than to leave them near the dock, so we walked down to the water, far away from the dock, near our camp and tied them to a tree.

About an hour goes by and Funk sees the tree they are tied to shaking and screams, "POSA!!! OTTERS!!!!" We both run down to the water and this is what we find.

Follow me on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/matthewposa/

snippet.title: Lake Superior Windstorm October 24th 2017
snippet.description:
I put on my rain gear and walked around Presque Isle park in Marquette, Michigan during a windstorm on October 24th 2017. 

I took extreme caution while recording making sure I had good footing and did not stand where water was sweeping.

I know the risks involved but this was something I wanted to see with my own eyes.

Follow me on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/matthewposa/
